  "text": "of younger patients in China. A Chinese study reported the incidence of young lung cancer population was 5.275% of overall lung cancer population [CITATION_1] . Risk factors of lung cancer in the general population include smoking status, air pollution, exposure to carcinogens (e.g. asbestos), and ionizing radiation [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , however, data regarding on young lung cancer patient subgroup are limited.",
